# Reconciled commit SHAs (Layer 3 skip list).
#
# Format: one short SHA per line, optionally followed by whitespace and a
# free-form note. Lines starting with '#' and blank lines are ignored.
#
# Append a SHA here to suppress that commit from daily_git_summary.sh
# entirely — both from any per-repo issue section AND from the (untracked)
# section. Use only for orphan commits (no #NN: prefix, no recoverable
# branch name) that have been retroactively attached to a GitHub issue via
# scripts/reconcile_commit.sh; never use for tracked commits, since that
# would erase legitimate evidence from the daily log.
#
# The reconcile_commit.sh helper appends here automatically after posting
# the verbose comment to the matching GitHub issue.
#
# Do not remove entries — once reconciled, the audit trail lives in the
# referenced issue's comment thread.
